 
<p>

<a href="https://www.commondreams.org/views/2022/07/09/dangerous-rise-gullible-american-cynic">"Gullible cynicism"</a>: the practice of bending over backwards to
disbelieve the generally accepted explanation for anything whatsoever,
while eagerly accepting absurdly implausible conspiracy theories
instead.
<p>
Gullible cynicism appeared long before there were modern
disinformation campaigns.  Nowadays it has spread beyond the US &mdash; but
gullible cynicism sure helps disinformation campaigns succeed.

 